com.shopgun.android.sdk.log

Class EventLog

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.shopgun.android.sdk.log.EventLog

  • public class EventLog
extends java.lang.Object
    EventLog class have been created to simplify logging within the ETA SDK. You will notice that this class is being used extensively throughout the SDK. And have been especially useful, while debugging networking issues.

    • Constructor Detail

      • EventLog

        public EventLog()
        Create a new EventLog, with no size limitations. Please be aware that these logs can grow to a considerable size, and may use an unreasonable amount of memory, and is therefore only recommended under development.

      • EventLog

        public EventLog(int logSize)
        Create a new log with a fixed size. The EventLig will be using FIFO ordering of events.
        Parameters:
        logSize - the desired size of the log

    • Method Detail

      • add

        public void add(java.lang.String name)
        Add a new Event to the log, based simply on a name. This is nice for tracing when, where and in what order the events have occurred.
        Parameters:
        name - of the log entry

      • add

        public void add(java.lang.String type,
                org.json.JSONObject data)
        Add a new Event to the log. Adding a special type, is nice for saving generic error correcting data to a log. This can be view, exception, or request events. but essentially any string will do.
        Parameters:
        type - of event to add
        data - data accompanying the event
